<br>
Recently there was an article(I'm afraid I've lost the link), that claimed that the Antarctic ice sheets were in fact growing. So why do you think this implies?<br>
<br>
On a related note, are you personally worried about global warming and climate change? Does it concern you that we may be more prone to storm conditions or extreme weather? Or is it just another stage in the Earth's evolution, and helpfull to agriculture(just think, vineyards on the South Downs).<br>
