<br>
I was being silly more than anything, because I've been enjoying the weather.<br>
<br>
Overall, it *is* something to be concerned about, but I doubt that in our lifetimes it will become a serious threat.<br>
<br>
When it comes to the Americans signing the treaty, we really have no say in whether or not it gets signed.  One thing I think many other people in the world don't understand is how freakin huge our country really is (Texas, which is only one of the fifty states, is roughly 3 times the size of the UK), and that it's run by-and-large by a bunch of old white men who are being payed to vote specific ways by corporations.  The system is corrupt, and there's little we can do to change it.  The old saying is very true - those who want power most likely are the ones who should be kept from it.<br>
<br>
I know that companies in our country do heinous things to the environment, and there are tons of activist groups that lobby to change that, but ultimately what is best for our nation's economy is what legislature will favor.<br>
<br>
I feel the need to stand up for other Americans here by saying that a lot of people do their part.  I for one recycle whenever there's a program in my area.  I don't litter, and I always spread the word about hybrid electric cars. (I want a Honda Civic Hybrid in the WORST way!!!) I always make sure my car meets EPA requirements, and I never use aerosol.<br>
<br>
The thing is, public transportation over here sucks!  Aside from a few cities (Boston, NY, Washington DC) most places you have to drive and park to get anywhere.  We built out, not up.  So until public transit is as effective and inexpensive as driving, Americans will be polluting w/ their cars.<br>
<br>
When it comes to the area of overpopulation, I firmly believe that one of 2 things should happen.  Either 1.) There should be some kind of rule saying that aside from miracle births, no family should birth more than 3 children (honestly, how many kids do you need?), OR Humanitarian aid regarding food supply should cease.  <br>
<br>
Regarding limits on pregnancies - I'm not suggesting that people not adopt - simply that a couple should not leave the world with twice (or more) the people they came in with.  <br>
<br>
Regarding the humanitarian aid stuff - I'm really with Malthus on this one, as harsh as it is.  Feeding and medicating hungry, ill people causes them to breed, which creates more hungry, ill people.  Stopping the aid means a fewer number of people die off from the lack of resources now than the ultimate die off would be when we finally cannot give any more support.<br>
<br>
Now that I'm certain I've opened at least 5 cans of worms, I'm going to watch TV. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/em/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Night! <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1><span class=m> </span></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub103.ezboard.com/us4turn3.showPublicProfile?language=EN>S4TuRn3</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0> </span><br> <span class=usertitle>Trickling Stream<br /><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-4-2.gif /></span><br>  ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.syntax-web.net/img/ffr.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top width=80% class=m><span class=title>   Re: No.....</span><br><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 6/18/02 9:58:26 am</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>    <hr size=1> ok, second very hot day ! At 6 am we had 25°C and now 28°C and they're barely awaiting for 40°C for the afternoon - worse than yesterday I can't believe it !<br>
