<br>
A couple of points have been brought up regarding future generations.<br>
<br>
 Now, assuming that global warming is actually taking place - should we act upon it, to preserve the climate for future generations, or should we let nature take its course and just learn to adapt? <br>
<br>
Should we feel responsible for what is happening to the climate, or is it just another of earth's cycles?<br>
<br>
 Do you feel it is immoral to perhaps not care or act, or are you quite content to live out your own lifespan(and perhaps your childrens) and thats all that you care about?<br>
