<br>
If you're a personal hedonic egoist, then fuck future generations, all that matters is what makes you happiest right now.<br>
<br>
If you're an act utilitarian, then you want to do what is going to make the most people happiest for the longest amount of time...<br>
<br>
And if you're a rule utilitarian then you want to do whatever is the best course of action if everyone were to do exactly what you were doing.<br>
<br>
The problem lies in the fact that there are so many personal philosophies that whether or not you feel that something should be done, it doesn't remotely guarnatee that anything will be done. <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1><span class=m> </span></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub103.ezboard.com/udashofmilk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DashOfMilk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.users.dialstart.net/~dashland/html/parent.gif" BORDER=0> </span><br> <span class=usertitle>Shimmering Ocean<br /><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-5.gif /></span><br> <BR><img src=http://www.users.dialstart.net/~dashland/html/lene1b.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top width=80% class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmmmm</span><br><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 6/18/02 11:25:12 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>    <hr size=1> but what would you do?<br>
